replies.bodyText:
Good catch! Two questions:

If we concat with failed Single, there is a chance that connection.closeAsync() may also fail. Should we worry about handling that case and adding the original exception as a suppressed one for the failed closure?
Should we make the same change for RRLB as a follow-up? Currently, we just subscribe to closeAsync and return an exception. For example: 


      servicetalk/servicetalk-loadbalancer/src/main/java/io/servicetalk/loadbalancer/RoundRobinLoadBalancer.java


        Lines 279 to 285
      in
      52532d4







           if (!selector.test(newCnx)) { 




               newCnx.closeAsync().subscribe(); 




               // Failure in selection could be temporary, hence add it to the queue and be consistent with the 




               // fact that select failure does not close a connection. 




               return failed(new ConnectionRejectedException("Newly created connection " + newCnx + 




                       " rejected by the selection filter.")); 




           }

